observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Accountant shall:

Enforce immediate settlement of outstanding cash advances totaling to ₱1,038,204.04 pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-002 and COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated February 10, 1997 and November 28, 2012, respectively;

Prioritize issuance of demand letters to all accountable officers still in active service; 

Impose the withholding of salary and the institution of other sanctions as provided under Item 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated           February 10, 1997; and

Prepare aging schedule of advances on a quarterly basis and indicate in the remark’s column the actual status of the accounts to support the request for write-off pursuant to Item 7.4 of COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to: 

Assess the manpower of the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to determine the needed personnel to undertake the activities of the office in improving the Municipality’s collection efficiency;

Direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to conduct intensive tax campaign and employ collection strategies to encourage the taxpayers to pay their taxes on time; 

Issue Notices of Delinquency and/or final demand letters to concerned property owners and avail remedies through levy on real property or judicial actions provided by RA No. 7160; and

Prepare a certified list of all real property tax delinquencies and post the said list at the Municipality and in publicly accessible and conspicuous place in each barangay and/or published the notice of delinquency in a newspaper of general circulation once a week for two consecutive weeks.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant shall:
Enforce immediate settlement of outstanding cash advances totaling to ₱1,038,204.04 pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-002 and COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated February 10, 1997 and November 28, 2012, respectively;
Prioritize issuance of demand letters to all accountable officers still in active service;
Impose the withholding of salary and the institution of other sanctions as provided under Item 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated           February 10, 1997; and
Prepare aging schedule of advances on a quarterly basis and indicate in the remarks column the actual status of the accounts to support the request for write-off pursuant to Item 7.4 of COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the Municipal Accountant:
Enforce immediate settlement of outstanding cash advances totaling ₱1,022,899.28 pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-02 and COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated February 10, 1997 and November 28, 2012, respectively; 

Prioritize issuance of demand letters to all accountable officers especially those with cash advances that have been outstanding for more than one year;

Impose withholding of salary and the application of other sanctions as provided under paragraphs 9.2 and 9.3 of COA Circular 97-002 dated February 10, 1997 to all active employees or still connected with the municipal government;

Assign personnel from the Accounting Office who will closely monitor the movement of the long outstanding cash advances and to prepare quarterly report copy furnished the Audit Team.

